The paper deals with privacy concerns in the context of smart meters, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a charging policy that involves coding strategies, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper deals with energy consumption, which could potentially fall under the categories of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
